Clinical Strategist
03 May 2014 06:24 PM - UAE
. Clinical StrategistAbout the JobThe Clinical Strategist is responsible for developing and driving successful clinical engagements through the application of Cerner's methodology in assigned implementation, sales, and marketing activities. On the Implementation side, the Clinical Strategist will engage client organization leadership to articulate vision, demonstrate benefits and localize change management strategies on their journey to automate clinical practice and business operations. The scope of responsibility includes, but is not limited to CPOE, Integrated Medication process and patient safety across the continuum of care via Role, Venue and Condition. The associate in this role will also conduct outcomes assessments and communicate key findings, conclusions, and recommendations to the executive and project leadership as well as assess organizational opportunities to improve quality of care and patient safety.Cerner Corporation, along with its subsidiaries and affiliates (Cerner), is proud to be an equal opportunity employer and a drug-free workplace.All employees must be legally authorized to work in the country where the position is located. If applicant lacks required authorization, work visa sponsorship may be available for this position.Be a part of something that matters.Â  Something that affects every single person, every single daypeople's health and the care they receive.Recognized as one of the most innovative companies in the world (#13 in 2013 by Forbes ), Cerner is transforming health care by developing tools and technologies that make it easier and more efficient for care providers and patients to navigate the complexity of our health.Â From single offices to entire countries, Cerner technology solutions are licensed by over 9,300 health care venues around the world.Minimum Quallifications:Bachelor's degree in NursingCurrent active licenseCurrent and all previous licensures in good standingMinimum five years clinical backgroundMinimum two years' experience as a clinical leaderExperience with automated workflow redesign and process improvementStrong understanding of healthcare strategy, operations and regulatory requirementsAnalytical skills including financial, process and risk analysisDeep understanding of all healthcare organizations including integrated delivery networks, community hospitals, academic and children's hospital systems and governmental entities Excellent presentation skillsSkilled in Microsoft Office Suite (specifically Excel, Word and PowerPoint)Preferred Qualifications:Preferred four plus years of healthcare management experienceExperience leading and/or facilitating organizational change preferably working with a cross-functional groupAdditional Information:Travel Percentage: 60%
